Question: How to get the value of a specific child in Firebase:
I'm trying to get the value of a specific child in Firebase. I have the following code:
DatabaseReference rootRef = FirebaseDatabase.getInstance().getReference();
ValueEventListener eventListener = new ValueEventListener() {
    @Override
    public void onDataChange(DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) {
        String value = dataSnapshot.child("childName").getValue(String.class);
        Log.d(TAG, "Value: " + value);
    }

    @Override
    public void onCancelled(DatabaseError databaseError) {
        Log.d(TAG, "Error: " + databaseError.getMessage());
    }
};
rootRef.addValueEventListener(eventListener);

This code works fine and I get the value of the "childName" child. However, I want to get the value of a child that is nested inside another child. For example, I have the following structure in my Firebase database:
{
  "parent" : {
    "child1" : "value1",
    "child2" : {
      "grandchild" : "value2"
    }
  }
}

How can I modify my code to get the value of "grandchild" child?
